PEOPLE: L.A. COUNTY 
James R. Brewer has been promoted to executive vice president-credit 
administration division manager for Mitsui Manufacturers Bank. He succeeds Yuji 
Okada, who has returned to the parent Mitsui Bank in Tokyo. Brewer has been 
responsible for Mitsui's loan adjustment and real estate special assets 
functions. In another move, Nobushige Sakurai, senior vice president and deputy 
general manager, has been promoted to general manager of the bank, replacing 
Kunio Nagasaki, executive vice president, who has returned to Tokyo. 
